<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0da24365-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21053"><num value="21053">§ 21053.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0da24366-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21053/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for grants under this subpart $10,000,000 for fiscal year 2003.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0da24367-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21053/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Availability of funds</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Amounts appropriated pursuant to the authorization under this section shall remain available, without fiscal year limitation, until expended.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0da24368-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tII/s283">Pub. L. 107–252, title II, § 283</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1702">116 Stat. 1702</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0da24369-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">
